The Police Command in Cross River State has read the riot act to suspected criminals who murdered four Policemen in Calabar, Cross River State capital. The Command in a press statement regretted the murder of the officers. “The Command is on a total clampdown drive on any person, group of persons and sponsors of all barbaric act against humanity without recourse. “It is worth noting that the Command has so far arrested five suspects in connection with the crime and will go all out to unravel the essence of this dastardly act ”The Command wishes to state equivocally that there is no cause for alarm, no tension in the state as published or claimed in some social media platforms. The Command urged members of the public to partner and collaborate with the police in information gathering and sharing for quality service delivery at all times